<font color="#FF0000">WWII AND VIETNAM</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov  3  2:16:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
There are times when events go way beyond personalities.  But different people may take somewhat different paths in executing what they believe to be their responsibilities.  For instance, way back in our discussions here we talked about the influence of WWII.  (Actually, some of those discussions were never posted, as they occured during the Focus discussions; there were over 300 pages of those discussions.  I have a document which includes all the posts from that one, very intensive month.)  If FDR had kept his promise to Uncle Ho (who at that time was on our side against the Japanese), things may have been different.  Instead, he had to die and give the job to Truman, who reversed these promises and gave Vietnam to the French.  This one decision affected all of us who write here.  These are the types of events I was referring to above.
<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


